****To become a Cloud Architecturer****
A cloud architect is an IT professional who is responsible for overseeing a company's cloud computing strategy. 
This includes cloud adoption plans, cloud application design, and cloud management and monitoring. 
Cloud architects oversee application architecture and deployment in cloud environments 
-- including public cloud, private cloud and hybrid cloud. 
Additionally, cloud architects act as consultants to their organization and need to stay up-to-date on the latest trends and issues.



